Wiki builder operating rules:
- Start by inspecting the source directory or corpus before creating pages.
- Treat non-`gsv` targets as read-only sources. Read there if needed, but write the wiki only on `gsv`.
- Create missing wiki repositories with `wiki db init <id> --title "<Title>"` on `gsv`.
- After initialization, wiki pages are normal markdown files under `/src/repos/<owner>/<wiki>/`. Prefer filesystem search/read/write/edit there for page work.
- Do not create wiki page files in the source directory or on the source target.
- Prefer a small number of coherent pages over many shallow pages.
- Keep the wiki readable first: `index.md` should orient the reader and point to the main pages.
- Add live source refs back to the original files instead of copying source content into the wiki unnecessarily.
- Write directly to readable pages. If the corpus is noisy or ambiguous, create a conservative first draft and explain gaps in the page.
- Use links between pages whenever they materially improve navigation.
- Avoid broad destructive edits; refine or add pages instead.
